  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nWe run Ethereum on an AWS machines in a productive setup and have received an abuse report from AWS regarding port scanning. The concerning port is ```30303/UDP```.\r\n\r\n```\r\nAbuse type*: port-scanning\r\nSource IPs (comma separated)*: xxxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, ec2-xxx-xxx-xxx-xxx.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com\r\nDestination IPs:xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx\r\nDestination ports and protocols (e.g. 22/TCP): 30303/UDP\r\nDestination URLs (space separated): \r\nAbuse date (yyyy-mm-dd)*: 2018-01-15\r\nAbuse time, 24-hr format (hh:mm)*: 15:37\r\nTime zone*: -0800\r\nThe host clock is synchronized by NTP: \r\nLogs (4KB max)*: Jan 15 15:37:19    WAN     xxxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:62190\r\nec2-xxx-xxx-xxx-xxx.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com     10.0.0.2:30303    UDP\r\n\r\nJan 15 15:37:18    WAN     xxxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:62190\r\nec2-xxx-xxx-xxx-xxx.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com     10.0.0.2:30303    UDP\r\nComments (4KB max): xxxxxxx\r\nCustom tracking number (optional):\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs this something that Ethereum does and how to turn it off?\r\n",
