    "body": "I had a similar problem at a different hoster -> https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/6386/how-to-prevent-being-blacklisted-for-running-an-ethereum-client/9945#9945  The only reliable way to solve this with geth was to use the firewall to block sending to private network addresses. In parity there is ``--allow-ips public``, but afaik there is nothing similar in geth. Maybe it would be a good thing to add such a flag to geth too.",
